rComments: Graded by 1 midterm, 1 final, 1 group project split into various individual- and group-based parts. Participation makes up 15% of the final mark. Exams were multiple choice and short answers but open book. Dr. McDonald is very responsive to all emails and questions, and her feedback is informative. She really wants you to succeed in class!

I loved taking this class with her. All of her assignments and examinations were very fair, she gave very clear expectations and rubrics, and she provided great opportunities to improve your grade through participation. Overall, I would highly recommend her -- she is kind, fair, and creates interesting lectures.

Margarethe is quite a kind and caring prof, but i found her lectures kinda boring, the readings she assigned were pretty neat tho. I wish she had told us about the huge group project earlier in the course, its worth so much of your grade and if you have poor group members you're really screwed over. overall would take her again for an easy a.

I really enjoyed her class. She truly is a SME and communicates the information clearly. There was a group project (I'm not a big fan of those) but it was interesting and didn't mind it. I would definitely recommend this prof.

The expectations for this course were clear, and exams covered the course content. The group project wasn't too easy and wasn't too hard, and you could take part of the Ventures Showcase to get an extra 1% + possibly win money. There's a lot of assignments and a lot to cover, but if you work for it you can get a great grade - she makes it possible.

Dr. McDonald is the most dedicated and the kindest prof I ever had. She gives really good feedback on all the assignments. There are a lot of very small assignments that help distribute the weight of the final mark. Everything is recorded so even if you can't make it to class you are not missing out. She always makes time to meet with students.

She has a complex lecture and many group assignments, which is hard to do within an online class, and the participant is required, you have a 1 %asignement in every live lecture. I think this class is boring and useless.
